RAINBOW ENERGY MARKETING CORPORATION FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF, VOLUME NO. 1
1. Availability: Rainbow Energy Marketing Corporation (Rainbow) makes electric energy and capacity available under this Rate Schedule for wholesale sales to purchasers with whom Rainbow has contracted.
2. Applicability: This Rate Schedule is applicable to all sales of electric energy or capacity by Rainbow not otherwise subject to a particular Rate Schedule of Rainbow.
3. Rates: All sales shall be made at rates established by agreement between the purchaser and Rainbow.
4. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions of sale shall be established by agreement between purchaser and Rainbow.
5. Ancillary Services.
PJM: Rainbow offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. ("PJM") and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection.
New York: Rainbow offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc.
New England: Rainbow offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc.
California: Rainbow offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation ("CAISO") and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO.
MISO: Rainbow offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (MISO) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO.
Southwest Power Pool: Rainbow offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (SPP) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP.
Third Party Provider:
Third-party ancillary services: Rainbow offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider's OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization..
6. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Rainbow shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Rainbow's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Rainbow to engage in affiliate sales under this tariff or otherwise restricts or limits Rainbow's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Rainbow's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this tariff.
7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Rainbow does not have any limitations on its market-based rate authority, except as otherwise provided in this Tariff. Rainbow has obtained waivers from Subparts B and C of Part 35, regarding the filing of tariffs, except sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; Part 41 regarding accounts, records and memoranda; Part 101, regarding Uniform System of Accounts with the exception that waiver of the provisions that apply to hydropower licensees has not been granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects; and Part 141 regarding statements and reports, except sections 141.14 and 141.15. Rainbow also has blanket approval under Part 34 of the Commission's regulations of future issuances regarding securities and assumption of liabilities. See Rainbow Energy Marketing Corporation, Docket No. ER94-1061-000, at 1 (June 10, 1994) (unpublished letter order).
8. Seller Category: Rainbow is a Category 2 seller in the Central Region and a Category 1 seller in the Northeast, Southeast, Southwest Power Pool, Southwest and Northwest regions, as defined in 18 CFR 35.36(a).
9. Communications: Except as otherwise agreed to in writing by the purchaser and Rainbow, any notice, demand, or request provided for in this Tariff shall be deemed to be properly given or made if set forth in writing and delivered or sent first class mail, postage prepaid, to Rainbow at its principal office or any purchaser when sales are made to wholesale purchasers under this Tariff.
10. Duration: This Tariff shall continue in effect until terminated or changed and such termination or change becomes effective in accordance with any applicable regulatory requirements.
11. Modifications: Rainbow may unilaterally apply, under Federal Power Act section 205 and the regulations promulgated thereunder, to the Commission or other regulatory agency having jurisdiction for a modification of this Tariff.
12. Effective Date: This Rate Schedule is effective on and after June 10, 1994.
